    <item>
      <title>SwanSong 0.3.1</title>
      <link>https://github.com/RegionallyFamous/SwanSong-Desktop/releases/tag/v0.3.1</link>
      <description sparkle:format="html">&lt;h2&gt;See exactly what changed.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SwanSong 0.3.1 turns Translation Lab into a workspace that remembers the whole investigation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keep every comparison.&lt;/strong&gt; Original and Patched frames, replay plans, bindings, and pixel differences stay together inside your project.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trace the pixels.&lt;/strong&gt; Select a rectangle to learn which layer, map cells, tiles, palette, and final writer produced it.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Play at your pace.&lt;/strong&gt; Observed sessions advance one visible step at a time while preserving clean from-boot proof.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Read without squinting.&lt;/strong&gt; Support, Privacy, and Acknowledgements now use real headings, lists, links, and spacing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Private by design. Detailed evidence stays in the project you choose.&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/RegionallyFamous/SwanSong-Desktop/releases/tag/v0.3.1"&gt;Read the full release notes.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
